Bretherick's Handbook of Reactive Chemical Hazards, the widely accepted and best-selling book, is now available in its Sixth Edition. It is essential for all those working with chemicals. Completely updated and revised, this successful two-volume book contains documented information on hazards and appropriate references. You will find specific information on the stability of the listed compounds, and the reactivity of mixtures of two or more compounds under various circumstances. Each compound is identified by an UPAC-based name, the CAS registry number, its empirical formula and its structure
